        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You often heard tales of the white faced terrors that swept across the plains, ripping families asunder, burning villages, and leavingly only distant screams for help to travel in the wind and the animals. But you didn't believe it until the bag was tossed on your head, and the wind carried your own horrified shreiks. The spirits were all that calmed you, and the lump of dirt mixed with your own blood and sweat. That ball of filth saved your life, as it brought on the vomitting. It worried your captors, and fearing your disease would spread, they threw you overboard into a tempest. The spirits guided you for two days and two nights through a neve ending gale. When you dragged yourself upon the sand, he stood over you, watching all the time that you struggled, impressed with your resolve to survive. He taught you how to ride the very waters that tried to claim you, teaching you a very old magic that belonged to only the oldest, and the strongest of the Koldunics. You learned how to calm the harshest waters, and throw the calmest seas into a frenzy, you practiced on scooners, sinking them into the ocean with a lazy swat of your hand. Your sires final gift to you was a way off the island, he taught you how to walk along the sea, hide amongst the deepest shadows at the bottom of the ocean floor, and you bid him farewell as you began your pilgrimage to the mainland. You don't know if he ever made it off the island, but when you touched down at least, you met Mosa, whom the spirits have told of your coming. He greeted you with enthusiasm to teach another the way of the spirits."
        ],
